                        <item xml:id="e1">- Fol. 2r: Crude drawing of a cross (?).&#xD;
- The title of the book is crudely written on fol. 2r.&#xD;
- The names of the donors are written on fol. 130vb.&#xD;
- A crude frame in red ink is drawn around four lines: fol. 59va.&#xD;
- Corrections written over erasures: e.g., fols. 15ab, 44rb, 52ra, 53vb, 54ra.&#xD;
- Omitted letters or words inserted interlineally: e.g., fols. 3rb, 4rb, 5ra, 6vb, 7vab.&#xD;
- Tämälläs-sign indicating the place where the omission, written in the outer or upper margin, belongs: e.g., fols. 9va, 13ra, 15va, 27ra, 29rb.&#xD;
- Compressed script: e.g., fols. 28vb-30ra, 47va-48va, 52vb-53va.&#xD;
- አም ቷቲ ሙአ አን ፋሲ (musical annotation signs?) is written in very small letters above the abbreviation ሃ፡ሃ፡ሃ፡ሃ፡: e.g., fols. 9vab, 10rab, 10vab, 12rab.</item>
                     </list>
